The claim: Disposable masks should be worn white-side-out to keep COVID-19 outAs total U.S. COVID-19 cases exceed 600,000 and deaths surpass 25,000, mask use is becoming increasingly common.
Amid the many conversations about face masks, misinformation about proper use continues to spread.
The claim that disposable masks should be reversed depending on the health of the wearer persists despite fact checks finding otherwise.
